 films in response to Olafur’s Little Sun solar-powered lamp highlighting deeper issues that their own country/culture face. I particularly loved ","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1,"offset":2163},"end":{"line":14,"column":338,"offset":2500},"indent":[]}},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Khavn de la Cruz’s humourous Solar Syokoy (Philippines)","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":340,"offset":2502},"end":{"line":14,"column":395,"offset":2557},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":338,"offset":2500},"end":{"line":14,"column":397,"offset":2559},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" about a Merman’s quest to find water in the urban city by using the Little Sun solar-lamp. ","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":397,"offset":2559},"end":{"line":14,"column":489,"offset":2651},"indent":[]}},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Darkness by visual artist/filmmaker Natasha Mendonca (India)","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":491,"offset":2653},"end":{"line":14,"column":551,"offset":2713},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":489,"offset":2651},"end":{"line":14,"column":553,"offset":2715},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" explores the nature of darkness as part of an everyday reality of the poor.","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":553,"offset":2715},"end":{"line":14,"column":629,"offset":2791},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1,"offset":2163},"end":{"line":14,"column":629,"offset":2791},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Olafur Eliasson said: ‘It has been a true gift to work on the sixteen Little Sun Films with these highly talented, very diverse filmmakers from all over the world, who have generously volunteered their voices and visions to this endeavour to bring light to some of the 1.6 billion people in the world without adequate access to the electrical grid. The responses have been unexpected, poetic, and eye-opening.’ ","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":2793},"end":{"line":16,"column":412,"offset":3204},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":2793},"end":{"line":16,"column":412,"offset":3204},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"emphasis","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Other Participating filmmakers are Mauro Andrizzi, Edwin, Hawa Essuman, Julio Hernández-Cordón,  Alejo Moguillansky, Omelga Mthiyane, Peter Tukei Muhumuza, Sherman Ong, Peru Ana Ana Peru, Kivu Ruhorahoza, Oscar RuizNavia, Dominga Sotomayor, Anocha Suwichakornpong, Susan Youssef and Man Kit Lam.","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":2,"offset":3207},"end":{"line":18,"column":297,"offset":3502},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1,"offset":3206},"end":{"line":18,"column":298,"offset":3503},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1,"offset":3206},"end":{"line":18,"column":298,"offset":3503},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"You can see all the short films at the ","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1,"offset":3505},"end":{"line":20,"column":40,"offset":3544},"indent":[]}},{"type":"link","title":null,"url":"http://www.littlesun.com/","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Little Sun website","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":41,"offset":3545},"end":{"line":20,"column":59,"offset":3563},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":40,"offset":3544},"end":{"line":20,"column":87,"offset":3591},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":".","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":87,"offset":3591},"end":{"line":20,"column":88,"offset":3592},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1,"offset":3505},"end":{"line":20,"column":88,"offset":3592},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"html","title":"Screenshot of the Little Sun Films from the Little Sun website. Copyright: Studio Olafur Eliasson","url":"./images/little-sun-films_vahcw5.jpg","alt":